"Narrated Aisha, Ummul Mu'minin: AbdulAziz ibn Jurayj said: I asked Aisha, mother of the believers: With which (surah) the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) used to observe witr? (She reported same as in the Hadith of Ubayy ibn Ka'b, No. 1418) This version adds: In the third rak'ah he would recite: \"Say, He is Allah, the One\" (Surah 112), and \"Say, I seek refuge in the Lord of daybreak\" (Surah 113), and \"Say, I seek refuge in the Lord of mankind\" (Surah)"